# Page Editing Rules

Follow the project workflow (rule 00) and CSS/Tailwind rules (rule 20). These rules add page-specific guardrails.

## Structure
- Preserve Eleventy front matter + existing `permalink` (unless explicitly moving a page).
- Use shared includes on full HTML pages: `partials/head-common.njk`, `partials/nav.njk`, `partials/footer.njk`.
- Keep `#scroll-progress`, `.aurora-bg`, and `/js/main.js` unless deliberately omitting.
- Reuse nearby sections/cards/markup before inventing new patterns.

## Visual Consistency (see AGENTS.md for full system)
- Default shell: `bg-gray-900 text-gray-200`.
- Headers: `.mv-page-header` + `.text-gradient`.
- Sections: `.mv-section`.
- Cards: `.mv-card` and/or `.glassmorphism` (existing padding/rounded/border/hover).
- Fonts: Inter (body), Playfair Display (headings). No new fonts.
- Accents: pink/gold primary; others only for status/category.

## Content, Safety, SEO, Accessibility
- Keep copy factual, concise, public-safe. No secrets, private data, financial advice, performance promises, or "buy/sell/hold" language.
- External links: `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`.
- New/major pages: match title, meta description, OG/Twitter, canonical (`https://www.messyvirgo.com/`), and structured data of nearby pages. Update `sitemap.xml.njk` when needed.
- Images: meaningful `alt` (unless purely decorative). Interactive elements need accessible text/`aria-label`.
- Responsive: mobile-first, no overflow/overlap/clipped text.
